%N A094255 Let M = the 3 X 3 matrix [ 0 1 0 / 0 0 1 / -1, 3*sqrt(3), 3]. M^n * [1 1 1] = [ p q r]; then a(n-1), a(n), a(n+1) = floor p, q, r, respectively.
%C A094255 The matrix M is derived from a polynomial shown on p. 208 of "Advanced Trigonometry": sqrt(3)*x^3 - 3x^2 - 3*sqrt(3)*x + 1, which has roots tan 10 deg., tan 70 deg. and tan 130 deg. a(n)/a(n-1) tends to tan 70 deg. = 2.747477419...; e.g. a(11)/a(10) = 32975 / 12004 = 2.7470009...
%D A094255 C. V. Durell, A. Robson, "Advanced Trigonometry", Dover 2003, p. 208.
%e A094255 a(4), a(5), a(6) = 28, 75, 211 = floor: p, q, r; where M^5 * [1 1 1] = [p q r].
